Version 1.2.8 (changes from 1.2.7) - Released 02/10/2014:
* Windows multi-flow execution: separate CMD for each CPU thread
* Fixed treatment of last element in generatorSingleI()

Version 1.2.7 (changes from 1.2.6) - Released 28/05/2014:
* Same print format for time elapsed as for estimated time left
* "_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64" define moved again to Makefile
* Fixed exit of all threads on SIGINT
* Fixed conversion of seconds to human legible format
* More accurate monitoring of speed (generation and writing)
* Disabled fclose() due to high load with big files: files are automatically closed on program exit
* Other small fixes and code reorganized

Version 1.2.6 (changes from 1.2.5) - Released 22/05/2014:
* Estimation of output file size
* Show writing speed
* Fixed thread signal handling: proper pause and restart
* Fixed Windows compatibility
* Removed singProc() for redundancy

Version 1.2.5 (changes from 1.2.4) - Released 16/05/2014:
* Process monitoring with threads: progress, speed, estimated time left
* Fixed thread pause and restart
* Fixed erroneus file opening in calc only mode
* Other small fixes
* Improved estimation of time left

Version 1.2.4 (changes from 1.2.3) - Released 11/05/2014:
* Output on split files: one per each process
* Code reorganized and modularized
* Bug fixes

Version 1.2.3 (changes from 1.2.2) - Released 17/04/2014:
* Iterative generators
* Program suspension: pause and restart (Ctrl+\)
* Program heading
* Version check
* Various bug fixes
* Large file support (>2GB)
* Pipe semaphores for file writes
* Forecast number of sequences

Version 1.2.2 (changes from 1.2.0) - Released 04/04/2014:
* Source modularity
* Proper time measurements (nanoseconds precision)
* Fixed splitting of job per each process
* Pipe semaphores for concurrent writes on inter-process shared pipes

Version 1.2.0 (changes from 1.1.0) - Released 21/03/2014:
* Multi-core CPU support: use of FORKs (Linux only)
* Pipe for interprocess comunication
* Performance efficiency 
* Optimized different functions for generation types

Version 1.1.0 (changes from 1.0.0) - Released 18/03/2014:
* Multi-core CPU support: use of PTHREAD library (Linux only) - deprecated (heavy read/write conflicts on threads' shared memory)
* Windows compatibilty

Version 1.0.0 - Released 14/03/2014:
* New complete code rewrite
* Characters set from file
* Signal handler (Linux only)
* Sequence lenght from arguments
* Modularity
* Limited set of characters, select from arguments

